PQClean uses the flags here as specified by `/proc/cpuinfo`. It uses those for the detection of support for each scheme. The flags used by the compiler, which is what OQS expects, unfortunately don't match up. Perhaps this would better be solved more generically by a function like below.

```
# Maps /proc/cpuinfo flags as used in `META.yml` to `-mFLAG` compiler flags.
MAPPING = {
    'bmi1': 'bmi',
}
def cpuinfo_flags_to_compiler_flags(flags):
        return [MAPPING.get(flag, flag) for flag in flags]
```

With regards to the upstream versions of Dilithium and Kyber in PQClean: Dilithium in PQClean already has OSX support, for Kyber we still need to apply the same set of patches. We would definitely welcome help there, as we obviously only have so much time and our contributions are mostly driven by our direct research needs — we need to write papers after all.
